---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Base title="What is Stratum? — Multi-Tenancy Library for Node.js" description="Stratum is an open-source multi-tenancy library for Node.js and TypeScript. Hierarchical tenants, config inheritance, three isolation strategies, GDPR compliance. Learn why we built it and how it works.">

<!-- Nav -->
<nav class="nav">
  <div class="nav-inner">
    <a href="/" class="nav-logo">
      <img src="/favicon.png" alt="Stratum" class="nav-logo-img" width="28" height="28" />
      Stratum
    </a>
    <div class="nav-links">
      <a href="/what-is-stratum" aria-current="page">What is Stratum?</a>
      <a href="/blog">Blog</a>
      <a href="https://docs.stratum-hq.org">Docs</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/stratum-hq/Stratum">GitHub</a>
      <button class="theme-toggle" id="theme-toggle" aria-label="Toggle theme">
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
          <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="5"/>
          <line x1="12" y1="1" x2="12" y2="3"/>
          <line x1="12" y1="21" x2="12" y2="23"/>
          <line x1="4.22" y1="4.22" x2="5.64" y2="5.64"/>
          <line x1="18.36" y1="18.36" x2="19.78" y2="19.78"/>
          <line x1="1" y1="12" x2="3" y2="12"/>
          <line x1="21" y1="12" x2="23" y2="12"/>
          <line x1="4.22" y1="19.78" x2="5.64" y2="18.36"/>
          <line x1="18.36" y1="5.64" x2="19.78" y2="4.22"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</nav>

<!-- Hero -->
<section class="wis-hero">
  <h1>What is <span class="accent">Stratum?</span></h1>
  <p class="wis-elevator">
    Stratum is an open-source multi-tenancy library for Node.js and TypeScript.
    It gives your application hierarchical tenants, config inheritance, permission delegation,
    three database isolation strategies, and GDPR compliance &mdash; so you never have to build
    multi-tenancy from scratch again.
  </p>
  <div class="wis-install">
    <code>npm install @stratum-hq/lib pg</code>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- The Problem -->
<section class="wis-section">
  <h2>The problem Stratum solves</h2>
  <p class="wis-intro">
    Every B2B SaaS team starts the same way: add a <code>tenant_id</code> column to every table.
    It works &mdash; until your product grows.
  </p>

  <div class="wis-timeline">
    <div class="wis-timeline-item">
      <div class="wis-timeline-marker"></div>
      <div class="wis-timeline-content">
        <h3>Day 1</h3>
        <p><code>tenant_id</code> on every table, manual WHERE clauses. Simple. Works fine.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wis-timeline-item">
      <div class="wis-timeline-marker wis-warning"></div>
      <div class="wis-timeline-content">
        <h3>Month 6</h3>
        <p>Enterprise customer needs custom configuration. You hand-roll config tables with no inheritance. Each customer is a special case.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wis-timeline-item">
      <div class="wis-timeline-marker wis-warning"></div>
      <div class="wis-timeline-content">
        <h3>Month 12</h3>
        <p>Compliance audit. You scramble to add audit logging, data export, and purge capabilities. Retroactively.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wis-timeline-item">
      <div class="wis-timeline-marker wis-danger"></div>
      <div class="wis-timeline-content">
        <h3>Month 18</h3>
        <p>Large customer demands data isolation. Painful migration from shared tables to schema-per-tenant. Three months of engineering work.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="wis-punchline">
    By month 18, your team has built a worse version of Stratum and spent 3+ months doing it.
    Stratum gives you all of this from day one.
  </p>
</section>

<!-- How It Works -->
<section class="wis-section wis-how">
  <h2>How Stratum works</h2>

  <div class="wis-feature-grid">
    <!-- Tenant Hierarchy -->
    <div class="wis-feature-card">
      <h3>Tenant hierarchy</h3>
      <p>
        Tenants form a tree. A root organization can have resellers, who have clients,
        who have teams. Config and permissions flow down the tree automatically.
      </p>
      <div class="wis-diagram">
<pre>
<span class="tree-root">AcmeSec</span>                    <span class="tree-meta">&larr; root</span>
<span class="tree-dim">&boxvr;&boxh;&boxh;</span> <span class="tree-mid">NorthStar MSP</span>             <span class="tree-meta">&larr; reseller</span>
<span class="tree-dim">&boxv;   &boxvr;&boxh;&boxh;</span> <span class="tree-leaf">client-alpha</span>
<span class="tree-dim">&boxv;   &boxur;&boxh;&boxh;</span> <span class="tree-leaf">client-beta</span>
<span class="tree-dim">&boxur;&boxh;&boxh;</span> <span class="tree-mid">Apex Partners</span>
<span class="tree-dim">    &boxur;&boxh;&boxh;</span> <span class="tree-leaf">client-gamma</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Config Inheritance -->
    <div class="wis-feature-card">
      <h3>Config inheritance</h3>
      <p>
        Set a value on the root tenant and every child inherits it automatically.
        Lock a key so children can't override it. Override it at any level when needed.
      </p>
      <div class="wis-diagram">
<pre>
root: <span class="tree-root">max_users = 1000</span>        <span class="tree-meta">&larr; set once</span>
  &boxvr;&boxh; child-a: <span class="tree-mid">inherits 1000</span>    <span class="tree-meta">&larr; automatic</span>
  &boxur;&boxh; child-b: <span class="tree-leaf">max_users = 500</span>  <span class="tree-meta">&larr; override</span>

root: <span class="accent">region = "eu" (locked)</span>  <span class="tree-meta">&larr; children cannot change</span></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Isolation Strategies -->
    <div class="wis-feature-card wis-feature-wide">
      <h3>Three isolation strategies</h3>
      <p>
        Choose per tenant. Mix strategies in a single deployment.
        Upgrade a tenant's isolation level without migrating data.
      </p>
      <div class="wis-isolation-grid">
        <div class="wis-isolation-item">
          <div class="wis-isolation-label">Shared RLS</div>
          <div class="wis-isolation-desc">Same tables, PostgreSQL Row-Level Security. Lowest cost, highest density.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="wis-isolation-item">
          <div class="wis-isolation-label">Schema</div>
          <div class="wis-isolation-desc">Separate schema per tenant. Stronger isolation, still one database.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="wis-isolation-item">
          <div class="wis-isolation-label">Database</div>
          <div class="wis-isolation-desc">Dedicated PostgreSQL instance. Maximum isolation for compliance.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Why We Built It -->
<section class="wis-section">
  <h2>Why we built Stratum</h2>
  <p>
    We've seen multi-tenancy pain firsthand &mdash; at security platforms (MSSP/MSP) where
    nested tenant hierarchies are the norm, and at B2B SaaS companies where enterprise
    customers demand isolation, custom config, and compliance.
  </p>
  <p>
    Every team we worked with had the same story: they started with <code>tenant_id</code>,
    then built config tables, then added audit logs, then scrambled for isolation &mdash;
    each time reinventing what should be infrastructure.
  </p>
  <p>
    The Node.js and TypeScript ecosystem has no dominant multi-tenancy library.
    The .NET world has <a href="https://abp.io" class="wis-link">ABP.IO</a>.
    Ruby has <a href="https://github.com/influitive/apartment" class="wis-link">Apartment</a>.
    Node.js developers roll their own every time. Stratum changes that.
  </p>
</section>

<!-- Comparison -->
<section class="wis-section">
  <h2>Stratum vs alternatives</h2>
  <div class="wis-table-wrapper">
    <table class="wis-comparison-table" aria-label="Comparison of multi-tenancy approaches">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th></th>
          <th>Stratum</th>
          <th>tenant_id column</th>
          <th>WorkOS / Frontegg</th>
          <th>Custom built</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="wis-feature-label">Tenant hierarchy</td>
          <td class="wis-yes">Yes (20 levels)</td>
          <td class="wis-no">No</td>
          <td class="wis-no">No</td>
          <td class="wis-partial">Build it yourself</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="wis-feature-label">Config inheritance</td>
          <td class="wis-yes">Built-in</td>
          <td class="wis-no">No</td>
          <td class="wis-no">No</td>
          <td class="wis-partial">Build it yourself</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="wis-feature-label">Isolation strategies</td>
          <td class="wis-yes">3 (RLS, schema, DB)</td>
          <td class="wis-partial">Manual RLS</td>
          <td class="wis-no">No</td>
          <td class="wis-partial">Build it yourself</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="wis-feature-label">GDPR compliance</td>
          <td class="wis-yes">Export + purge</td>
          <td class="wis-no">No</td>
          <td class="wis-partial">Partial</td>
          <td class="wis-partial">Build it yourself</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="wis-feature-label">Audit logging</td>
          <td class="wis-yes">Built-in</td>
          <td class="wis-no">No</td>
          <td class="wis-partial">Auth events only</td>
          <td class="wis-partial">Build it yourself</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="wis-feature-label">Time to implement</td>
          <td class="wis-yes">60 seconds</td>
          <td class="wis-partial">1 day</td>
          <td class="wis-partial">1 week</td>
          <td class="wis-no">3+ months</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="wis-feature-label">Open source</td>
          <td class="wis-yes">MIT</td>
          <td class="wis-yes">N/A</td>
          <td class="wis-no">Proprietary</td>
          <td class="wis-yes">Yours</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Getting Started -->
<section class="wis-section wis-getting-started">
  <h2>Get started in 5 lines</h2>
  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-dot"></span>
      <span class="code-block-dot"></span>
      <span class="code-block-dot"></span>
      <span class="code-block-filename">quickstart.ts</span>
    </div>
    <pre set:html={`<span class="kw">import</span> &#123; Pool &#125; <span class="kw">from</span> <span class="str">"pg"</span>;
<span class="kw">import</span> &#123; Stratum &#125; <span class="kw">from</span> <span class="str">"@stratum-hq/lib"</span>;

<span class="kw">const</span> stratum = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="fn">Stratum</span>(&#123; pool: <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="fn">Pool</span>(), autoMigrate: <span class="num">true</span> &#125;);
<span class="kw">await</span> stratum.<span class="fn">initialize</span>();

<span class="cm">// Create a tenant and set config</span>
<span class="kw">const</span> org = <span class="kw">await</span> stratum.<span class="fn">createOrganization</span>(&#123; name: <span class="str">"Acme Corp"</span>, slug: <span class="str">"acme"</span> &#125;);
<span class="kw">await</span> stratum.<span class="fn">setConfig</span>(org.id, <span class="str">"max_users"</span>, &#123; value: <span class="num">100</span> &#125;);
<span class="cm">// That's it. Multi-tenancy with config inheritance, ready to go.</span>`} />
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section class="cta">
  <div class="cta-inner fade-in">
    <h2>Ready to stop reinventing <span class="accent">multi-tenancy?</span></h2>
    <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content: center;">
      <a href="https://docs.stratum-hq.org/getting-started/quick-start" class="btn-primary">Get Started</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/stratum-hq/Stratum" class="btn-secondary">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Footer -->
<footer class="footer">
  <div class="footer-inner">
    <p class="footer-meta">
      MIT License &middot; &copy; <a href="https://github.com/stratum-hq">Stratum HQ</a>
    </p>
    <div class="footer-links">
      <a href="https://docs.stratum-hq.org">Docs</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/stratum-hq/Stratum">GitHub</a>
      <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/org/stratum-hq">npm</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</footer>

<style>
  /* What-is-Stratum page styles */
  .wis-hero {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: calc(var(--space-8) * 3) var(--space-6) var(--space-8);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .wis-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .wis-elevator {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .wis-install {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-6);
    background: var(--code-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--code-text);
  }

  .wis-section {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-6);
  }

  .wis-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .wis-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .wis-section code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875em;
    color: var(--sandstone);
    background: var(--code-bg);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .wis-intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .wis-punchline {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .wis-timeline {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 2rem;
    margin: var(--space-6) 0;
  }

  .wis-timeline::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 7px;
    top: 4px;
    bottom: 4px;
    width: 2px;
    background: var(--border);
  }

  .wis-timeline-item {
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .wis-timeline-marker {
    position: absolute;
    left: -2rem;
    top: 6px;
    width: 16px;
    height: 16px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--surface-2);
    border: 2px solid var(--sandstone);
  }

  .wis-timeline-marker.wis-warning {
    border-color: var(--warning);
  }

  .wis-timeline-marker.wis-danger {
    border-color: var(--error);
    background: var(--accent-muted);
  }

  .wis-timeline-content h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .wis-timeline-content p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Feature grid */
  .wis-feature-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .wis-feature-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .wis-feature-card {
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: var(--space-6);
  }

  .wis-feature-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .wis-feature-card p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .wis-feature-wide {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
  }

  .wis-diagram {
    background: var(--code-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: var(--space-4);
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .wis-diagram pre {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  /* Isolation grid */
  .wis-isolation-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .wis-isolation-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .wis-isolation-item {
    background: var(--surface-2);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: var(--space-4);
  }

  .wis-isolation-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--sandstone);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .wis-isolation-desc {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
  }

  /* Comparison table */
  .wis-table-wrapper {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: var(--space-4) 0;
  }

  .wis-comparison-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .wis-comparison-table th {
    text-align: left;
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .wis-comparison-table th:first-child {
    min-width: 140px;
  }

  .wis-comparison-table td {
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .wis-feature-label {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .wis-yes {
    color: var(--success);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .wis-no {
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
  }

  .wis-partial {
    color: var(--warning);
  }

  .wis-link {
    color: var(--sandstone);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .wis-link:hover {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* Getting Started */
  .wis-getting-started {
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  .wis-getting-started h2 {
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>

<!-- Theme toggle (same as homepage) -->
<script>
  const toggle = document.getElementById('theme-toggle');
  const html = document.documentElement;

  function setTheme(theme: string) {
    html.setAttribute('data-theme', theme);
    localStorage.setItem('theme', theme);
  }

  const saved = localStorage.getItem('theme');
  if (saved) setTheme(saved);

  toggle?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const current = html.getAttribute('data-theme');
    setTheme(current === 'light' ? 'dark' : 'light');
  });
</script>

</Base>
